---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="sixpack CLI Commands" description="Current sixpack CLI command surface.">
  <article class="doc-page">
    <section class="doc-hero">
      <div class="doc-wrap">
        <p class="doc-kicker">/ cli</p>
        <h1 class="doc-title">A small binary surface while the engine settles.</h1>
        <p class="doc-lead">
          The current command line stays intentionally narrow. The runtime API
          and storage engine are the primary implementation focus, so the binary
          only exposes stable behavior that actually exists.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-block">
      <div class="doc-wrap doc-split">
        <div class="doc-panel">
          <h2>Implemented</h2>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><code>sixpack --version</code> or <code>sixpack -V</code> prints the CLI version.</li>
            <li><code>sixpack help</code>, <code>-h</code>, or <code>--help</code> prints usage.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-panel">
          <h2>Planned</h2>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>initialize a database directory</li>
            <li>inspect schema and storage status</li>
            <li>rebuild generated indexes</li>
            <li>repair or truncate incomplete final writes</li>
            <li>run focused benchmarks or diagnostics</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
